history.content:
I've taken them all. EE 126 is like 20-30% harder than CS 70; workload is slightly more, but EE 126 covers a lot of topics and the the people taking 126 tend to be the ones who did very well in 70.

EE 127 is conceptually dense, so it's like EE 126 conceptually, but homeworks are every two weeks so the workload is probably 30-40% less than CS 70.

Im thinking of taking these two classes next semester and I want an idea of what the workload will be like for each of them, maybe in terms of cs 61b and 70 since those are the only two heavy technicals I've taken if thats useful. Thanks!
history.subject: Workload of ee 126 and 127
